The general consensus among anatomists consulted is that there is no parasympathetic innervation of the ovary in humans. However, in rats, Gerendai and colleagues have provided evidence of a parasympathetic innervation of the ovaries using transsynaptic tracing techniques. We added the projections represented in Figure 1 of Gerendai (2002) et al Microscopy Research and Technique Volume 59, Issue 6 p. 474-483 but note that transsynaptic tracing studies can be difficult to interpret and that additional evidence may be needed.
